<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="133" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="133">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="133">
The generic name is a combination of Greek, micro (
<normalizedToken originalValue="mikrós">mikros</normalizedToken>
) = small, related to the small size of the adult type-specimen, and 
<taxonomicName lsidName="plecostomus" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" rank="species" species="plecostomus">plecostomus</taxonomicName>
= a former generic name of species currently included in 
<taxonomicName family="Loricariidae" lsidName="" pageId="4" pageNumber="133" rank="family">Loricariidae</taxonomicName>
, also in reference to the small adult size of the type-species. A masculine name.
</paragraph>
